  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6571.86 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6574 in PIN regime, dealers are currently buying the dip as they're long gamma and providing stabilizing flow. The massive +68.2B gamma wall at 6580 creates a strong magnet effect above current levels, while the wall break event suggests we just pushed through a key level - expect mean reversion back toward the 6574-6580 zone as dealers hedge against the move.\n\nWatch for continued dealer buying support into any weakness toward 6570 (30.8B wall) and selling pressure if we rally back above 6574 flip toward the 6580 max gamma strike where dealer selling intensifies.",
